(1, 1, 'Nantes', 'Metier', '<p>Oh, ow! Did you dress her up like this? Well, we did do the nose. Who\'s that then?</p>\n<p>What a strange person. Bring her forward! No, no, no! Yes, yes. A bit. But she\'s got a wart. Where\'d you get the coconuts? …Are you suggesting that coconuts migrate?</p>\n<p>Why? Who\'s that then? Burn her anyway! The Lady of the Lake, her arm clad in the purest shimmering samite, held aloft Excalibur from the bosom of the water, signifying by divine providence that I, Arthur, was to carry Excalibur. That is why I am your king.</p>\n<p>Why do you think that she is a witch? Well, we did do the nose. You don\'t frighten us, English pig-dogs! Go and boil your bottoms, sons of a silly person! I blow my nose at you, so-called Ah-thoor Keeng, you and all your silly English K-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-niggits!</p>\n<p>Burn her! We shall say \'Ni\' again to you, if you do not appease us. Well, I didn\'t vote for you. We want a shrubbery!! Listen. Strange women lying in ponds distributing swords is no basis for a system of government. Supreme executive power derives from a mandate from the masses, not from some farcical aquatic ceremony.</p>\n<ol>\n\n    <li>She looks like one.</li><li>Burn her!</li><li>Be quiet!</li>\n\n</ol>\n\n<p>Well, I got better. You don\'t vote for kings. The Knights Who Say Ni demand a sacrifice! Well, how\'d you become king, then? Shh! Knights, I bid you welcome to your new home. Let us ride to Camelot! Where\'d you get the coconuts?</p>\n<p>He hasn\'t got shit all over him. How do you know she is a witch? Be quiet! He hasn\'t got shit all over him. Shut up! Will you shut up?!</p>\n<ul>\n\n    <li>…Are you suggesting that coconuts migrate?</li><li>On second thoughts, let\'s not go there. It is a silly place.</li><li>The Lady of the Lake, her arm clad in the purest shimmering samite, held aloft Excalibur from the bosom of the water, signifying by divine providence that I, Arthur, was to carry Excalibur. That is why I am your king.</li>\n\n